Orestion was the work of seven angele, who also made man, a frail creature unable to do more than wriggle on the ground like a worm until raised by the Suprema Power. The same myth as to the creation of man is attributed below (chap. 5) and in Iren. i. 28. 3 to the Ophites, in whose system however the seven sons of Sophia-Prunikos replaoe the seven mester angele oi Saturninus. A close affinity can be traced throughout between the Irenaean Ophites and Saturninus, the latter no doubt having evolved the original and simpler clemente of the system, Saturninus‘ Christology was Boeotio, his rule of life Encratite.
